https://github.com/spulec/freezegun/commit/4b4ba0e2a14c1ecd7e8bfc0b2ea1f332840f5568 changed the class decorator to use `.mro()` which broke the support for decorating an old style class in Python 2.

Just having plain classes and omitting object is a common pattern in pytest tests:
```python
@freeze_time('2015-12-24')
class Test_Something:
    def test_foo(self):
        ...
```

This is not a problem in Python 3 since there are no old style classes. I have a patch which addresses this, will soon publish a PR.

